label: University of Pennsylvania LJS 221: Mémoire sur les rapports qui existent entre le calcul des résidus et le calcul des limites
attribution: Provided by the University of Pennsylvania Libraries
description:
Summary: Mathematical work on the calculus of residues and the calculus of limits, related to complex function theory. Between the first and second gatherings of the manuscript (following p. 8), a mechanical reproduction of another manuscript by Cauchy, titled Sur un nouveau principe de mécanique, is bound in.
        Language: French
        Support: paper
        Extent: 
        Collation: Paper, i + 46 + i; 1⁴ 2⁶ 3-11⁴; [1-2], 3-8, [i-ii, 1], 2-9, [10], 9-80, contemporary pagination in ink, upper center.
        Layout: Text written in 28 long lines, with numerous equations.
        Script: Written in cursive script, probably in the hand of Augustin Louis Cauchy.
        Decoration: 
        Binding: Contemporary (mid-19th-century) marbled paper over boards; parchment spine with Cauchy written in ink.
        Origin: Written in Turin, presented at the Academy of Sciences of Turin, 27 Nov. 1831 (title page, p. 1).
        Cite as:	
        UPenn LJS 221
        For catalog record, see Permanent Link: 5885633 http://hdl.library.upenn.edu/1017/d/medren/5885633
  For TEI description and digital images, see: http://openn.library.upenn.edu/Data/LJSchoenbergManuscripts/html/ljs221.html
